('fc9596d9-d60a-4faa-9f47-ec8ae95f645b', 'Cellucor SuperHD: Budget Energy and Fat Loss', 'A dual-purpose fat burner combining thermogenics with cognitive enhancers at an accessible price. Good for gym energy, modest for fat loss.', 'Caffeine provides the primary thermogenic and focus effects. Green Tea Extract and Capsimax support fat oxidation. Amla Fruit Extract provides antioxidant support.', ARRAY['Combines fat burning with focus', 'Affordable pricing', 'Trusted Cellucor brand', 'Available in stores everywhere'], 'Take 1 capsule twice daily before meals. Do not exceed 2 capsules.', ARRAY['Uses proprietary blends', 'Moderate caffeine content', 'Not as potent as premium options'], 'Casual gym-goers wanting a boost of energy and mild fat-burning support at a budget price.', 'Instant Knockout for serious fat loss. C4 for pre-workout energy.', 'Q: Does it really help with fat loss? A: It provides modest support mainly through caffeine and thermogenic compounds. Q: Can I take it with C4? A: Be careful of total caffeine intake if stacking.', 7.6, '[{"name": "Ashley P.", "rating": 4, "text": "Good energy for the gym at a great price. Not the strongest fat burner but I noticed a difference.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-03"}, {"name": "Jason W.", "rating": 3, "text": "Decent budget option. The energy boost is real but fat loss effects are subtle.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-14"}]'::jsonb),

('ae7aefc1-5778-499b-9a6f-7755aea76093', 'Garden of Life Vitamin Code: RAW Whole-Food Vitamins', 'The gold standard in whole-food multivitamins. Every nutrient is RAW food-created with live probiotics and enzymes for optimal absorption.', 'All vitamins are derived from 23 organically grown fruits and vegetables. Includes live probiotics for gut health and enzymes for nutrient absorption.', ARRAY['RAW whole food sourced', 'Includes probiotics and enzymes', 'Non-GMO Project Verified', 'No synthetic fillers or binders'], 'Take 4 capsules daily, 2 with breakfast and 2 with lunch.', ARRAY['4 capsules per day', 'Larger capsule size', 'Must refrigerate after opening'], 'Men wanting the highest quality whole-food sourced multivitamin with digestive support.', 'Thorne for bioactive synthetics. Ritual for targeted nutrients. MegaFood for another whole-food option.', 'Q: Are whole-food vitamins better absorbed? A: Research suggests food-based nutrient complexes may be better recognized by the body. Q: Why refrigerate? A: To maintain the viability of live probiotics.', 8.6, '[{"name": "Dave R.", "rating": 5, "text": "The probiotics and enzymes make this feel like actual food nutrition. My digestion improved noticeably.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-10"}, {"name": "Scott M.", "rating": 4, "text": "Premium quality you can feel. 4 capsules is a lot but the whole-food sourcing is worth it.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-26"}]'::jsonb),

('a467e036-af34-4c55-96dc-b735c9f11807', 'Life Extension Two-Per-Day: Science-Optimized Multi', 'Dramatically higher potencies than mass-market multis with bioactive vitamin forms. Outstanding value for science-minded supplementers.', 'Uses 5-MTHF folate (800mcg), methylcobalamin B12, mixed tocopherols vitamin E, and chelated minerals. Doses are significantly higher than Centrum and similar products.', ARRAY['High-potency bioactive forms', 'Only 2 capsules daily', 'Excellent value for quality', 'Based on latest research'], 'Take 1 capsule with breakfast and 1 with lunch for steady nutrient levels.', ARRAY['No iron by design', 'Not whole-food sourced', 'May be excessive for some nutrients'], 'Science-minded supplement users who want optimal forms and higher potencies than mainstream multivitamins.', 'Thorne for practitioner-grade. Garden of Life for whole-food sourced. Nature Made for budget.', 'Q: Why no iron? A: Most adults get adequate iron from diet and excess can cause oxidative damage. Q: Is it better than Centrum? A: Significantly higher potencies and superior vitamin forms in virtually every category.', 8.6, '[{"name": "Robert C.", "rating": 5, "text": "The best value premium multi on the market. Bioactive forms at these doses for under $20 per month is unbeatable.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-08"}, {"name": "Linda K.", "rating": 4, "text": "My naturopath recommended Life Extension. The quality is excellent and only 2 pills is convenient.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-22"}]'::jsonb),

('487bce0c-8a38-4bdd-bf82-1afd1417e04a', 'AG1: The Premium All-in-One Greens Powder', 'AG1 is the most popular greens supplement in the world. One scoop provides 75 vitamins, minerals, probiotics, and adaptogens. Premium pricing but unmatched comprehensiveness.', '75 ingredients across vitamins, minerals, prebiotics, probiotics, adaptogens, superfoods, and digestive enzymes. Third-party tested by NSF.', ARRAY['All-in-one nutritional insurance', '75 ingredients per scoop', 'Third-party tested', 'Replaces multiple supplements'], 'Mix 1 scoop with 8-10 oz cold water first thing in the morning on an empty stomach.', ARRAY['Very expensive ($3+ per serving)', 'Subscription model preferred', 'Individual nutrient doses may be low', 'Some proprietary blends'], 'Health optimizers willing to invest in a single-scoop solution that covers multiple supplement categories.', 'Thorne Multi for a focused multivitamin. A dedicated probiotic + multi combo for better individual dosing.', 'Q: Can AG1 replace my multivitamin? A: It covers the basics but individual nutrient doses are lower than standalone supplements. Q: Why is it so expensive? A: 75 quality-sourced ingredients with third-party testing add up.', 8.2, '[{"name": "Jordan B.", "rating": 5, "text": "The convenience of one scoop replacing 5 supplements is worth the price for me. My energy is notably better.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-12"}, {"name": "Michelle S.", "rating": 4, "text": "Good product but expensive. I use it when traveling and switch to individual supplements at home.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-20"}]'::jsonb),

('73bc77cb-c0a6-47b3-9d2c-417219d2f921', 'NOW Adam: Best Value Men''s Multi', 'Comprehensive men''s formula including prostate and heart support at a fraction of premium competitors. Excellent quality-to-price ratio from a GMP-certified brand.', 'Full vitamin spectrum with added Saw Palmetto for prostate health, Plant Sterols for cholesterol, Lycopene for prostate, and CoQ10 for energy.', ARRAY['Excellent value for money', 'Includes prostate support', 'GMP certified facility', 'Comprehensive formula'], 'Take 2 softgels daily with a meal.', ARRAY['Large softgel size', 'Some synthetic vitamin forms', 'Contains soy'], 'Budget-conscious men who want comprehensive coverage including prostate and heart support.', 'Thorne Multi for premium quality. Garden of Life for whole-food. Kirkland for even cheaper.', 'Q: How does it compare to One A Day? A: More comprehensive with added prostate and heart support at a similar price. Q: Is the soy content concerning? A: The amount is minimal and not a concern for most people.', 8.2, '[{"name": "James F.", "rating": 5, "text": "Best bang for the buck men''s multi. The saw palmetto and CoQ10 are great bonuses at this price.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-06"}, {"name": "Mike N.", "rating": 4, "text": "Solid quality from NOW Foods. The softgels are big but easy to swallow with water.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-17"}]'::jsonb),

('b1b1f7f8-f2e5-47df-a7ec-907a68a862c0', 'Kirkland Daily Multi: Unbeatable Value', 'The ultimate budget multivitamin. USP Verified for quality assurance at just pennies per day. Covers all the basics reliably.', 'Full A-Z vitamin and mineral coverage. USP Verified ensures what is on the label is in the product. Basic but effective synthetic vitamin forms.', ARRAY['Pennies per day', 'USP Verified', 'Full vitamin spectrum', '500 count lasts over a year'], 'Take 1 tablet daily with food.', ARRAY['Basic synthetic forms', 'No extras like probiotics', 'Requires Costco membership', 'Large tablet'], 'Budget shoppers who want reliable, verified nutritional coverage at the lowest possible cost.', 'Nature Made for USP verified at more stores. NOW Adam for added men''s support.', 'Q: Is cheap bad? A: Not with USP verification. It guarantees potency and purity regardless of price. Q: Is it as good as Thorne? A: The nutrients are less bioavailable forms, but for basic coverage it is excellent.', 7.8, '[{"name": "Paul H.", "rating": 5, "text": "500 tablets for under $15. USP verified. You literally cannot beat this value.", "verified": true, "date": "2026-01-02"}, {"name": "Karen W.", "rating": 4, "text": "My pharmacist said Kirkland and Nature Made are the best budget options because of USP verification. Hard to argue.", "verified": true, "date": "2025-12-13"}]'::jsonb);